        <item>
            <title>1.0.0</title>
            <pubDate>Thu, 05 Feb 2026 13:43:24 +0100</pubDate>
            <sparkle:version>5</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.0.0</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<h3>1.0.0: The Official Release</h3>

<p>
  Thaw has reached its first stable milestone! This release consolidates all the
  progress from the beta period into a polished, reliable menu bar manager.
</p>

<p><strong>Latest Improvements (since beta 4):</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Enhanced Reliability:</strong> Stabilized HIDEventManager logic to
    prevent "show on hover" and "show on click" from stopping after repeated use
    and prevent saving chevron divider position which could leave Thaw in an
    unusable state.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>UI Polish:</strong> Condensed the menu bar tooltip for a cleaner
    look and added explicit double-click instructions.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>System Safety:</strong> Improved thread safety by synchronizing
    access to the cursor hide count.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Apple Menu Fix:</strong> Refined synthetic press offsets to ensure
    Thaw never accidentally triggers the Apple menu.
  </li>
</ul>

<hr />

<p><strong>Highlights from the Journey to 1.0:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>The Big Thaw:</strong> Successfully forked and rebranded with a new
    identity, app icon, and independent bundle ID
    (<code>com.stonerl.Thaw</code>).
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Ice Migration:</strong> Built-in support to import your old settings
    and control item positions from Ice.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Advanced Control:</strong> Introduced "Double-Click to Reveal" for
    always-hidden items and "Smart Rehide" strategies.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Modern macOS Support:</strong> Optimized for stability on macOS 26.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Performance:</strong> Faster icon caching, display-aware state
    refreshing, and thread-safe operations.
  </li>
</ul>

<hr />

<p><strong>Known Issues:</strong></p>
<p>
  If you are currently on macOS 14 or 15, please be aware that
  <strong>Thaw</strong> currently has some known bugs regarding temporary icons
  in the floating <strong>Thaw bar</strong>.
</p>
<p>
  I am actively investigating these issues and will release a fix as soon as
  possible. You can track the progress of this issue here:
  <a href="https://github.com/stonerl/Thaw/issues/1">GitHub Issue #1</a>.
</p>

<p>
  <em
    >Thank you for all the feedback during the beta period that made this
    release possible!</em
  >
</p>
]]></description>
