        <item>
            <title>1.0.0-beta.4</title>
            <pubDate>Tue, 03 Feb 2026 17:13:04 +0100</pubDate>
            <sparkle:channel>beta</sparkle:channel>
            <sparkle:version>4</sparkle:version>
            <sparkle:shortVersionString>1.0.0-beta.4</sparkle:shortVersionString>
            <sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>14.0</sparkle:minimumSystemVersion>
            <description><![CDATA[<h3>1.0.0-beta.4: Precision & Control</h3>

<p><strong>New Features:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Double-Click to Reveal:</strong> You can now double-click the Thaw
    icon to instantly reveal your "always-hidden" menu bar section.
  </li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Improvements & Fixes:</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>
    <strong>Smarter Temporary Items:</strong> Temporarily shown icons now rehide
    immediately when you switch applications, in addition to the standard timer.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>macOS 14/15 Stability:</strong> Fixed an issue where rehiding items
    could accidentally trigger the Apple menu.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Icon Placement:</strong> Improved logic to prevent "jiggling" and
    placement errors on older macOS versions when the control item is at the far
    left.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Search Cleanup:</strong> The search field now automatically clears
    itself whenever you close the search panel.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Reliable Migration:</strong> Enhanced the Ice settings detection
    logic to ensure the importer only appears when valid data is found.
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>UI Refinement:</strong> Cleaned up copyright strings and optimized
    how items return to their original sections after being temporarily visible.
  </li>
</ul>
]]></description>
